### **Seeing Your Value**

Before you can transform your economics, you must see what you actually create:

**If you're a caregiver** (nurse, teacher, parent, elder-care):
- Your care creates value the system doesn't pay for
- Every patient comforted, student taught, child raised
- The network will witness and accumulate recognition
- Your contribution has been invisible—until now

**If you're a maker** (repair, craft, build, grow):
- Your creation extends life, prevents waste, builds resilience
- Every device repaired, food grown, structure built
- The network will document environmental and community value
- Your skill has been undervalued—until now

**If you're a creator** (code, write, teach, design):
- Your work helps people you'll never meet
- Every tutorial, tool, design, documentation
- The network will maintain your presence and accumulate recognition
- Your contribution has been extracted—until now

**If you're a connector** (organize, coordinate, translate, mediate):
- Your relationships enable others to flourish
- Every introduction made, conflict resolved, coordination achieved
- The network will recognize relational value
- Your labor has been invisible—until now

### **Joining the Network**

The transition is gradual, not sudden:

**Phase 1: Visibility** (Month 1-3)
- Install the network interface
- Begin documenting your value creation
- See your REA flows for the first time
- Connect with others in your community

**Phase 2: Recognition** (Month 4-6)
- Accumulate tokens from your contribution
- Earn skill attestations from witnessed work
- Establish creator presence for your content
- Begin exchanging within the network

**Phase 3: Transition** (Month 7-12)
- Shift income partially to network economy
- Join or form cooperatives in your sector
- Reduce dependency on extraction channels
- Build resilient alternatives

**Phase 4: Liberation** (Year 2+)
- Network economy provides majority of income
- Old system becomes supplementary
- Community coordination replaces corporate dependency
- Value flows to contribution, not extraction

